{
  "stem": "19218.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And all-- when-- when you died, all you had to do is throw the guys out-- out of the barracks in a-- a little buggy, two-wheeled buggy would come along with-- with prisoners pushing it and collect all the corpses and take them off.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because they were burning them, taking them to the crematoriums.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And again, I must tell you, those people were probably the lucky ones.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because there were many times-- oh, yes, even the first night of arrival in there-- a lot of the people, maybe they knew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I don't know why, but they started running and they ran towards the barbed wires.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And of course, there were-- those were electric, electrified wires.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And of course, they were just-- all you could hear is the screaming and they were electrocuted right there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And later on after being in the camps, I wondered whether those were the lucky ones that didn't have to go through what we went through, that they died instantly.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We couldn't even think of our parents, sisters, brothers, cousins.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You have become the number one to survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You were worried strictly about yourself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We learned very fast what happened to the other people, what happened to our loved ones.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You could smell the stench of the-- of the burning of the flesh which was going on day and night, day and night constantly.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we knew exactly when transports would arrive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then especially being in Birkenau, I was there at the same time the gypsies were there, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they have liquidated-- one morning, we woke up and there was not a trace of the-- we were right across from each other.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The gypsy camp was liquidated completely and there were many, many young-- young people, young persons.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
